Rumph and Associates, P.C. is seeking a Data Manager to provide information management, guidelines, and training material development, statistical support, and technical assistance that support the President’s Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR) prioritization of population-based, HIV-focused household surveys as a means of monitoring HIV incidence, prevalence, and progress.
RESPONSIBILITIES
Data Management: Staff and development support to ensure efficient and secure data storage and accessibility. It includes data consolidation, processing, storage, and retrieval as well as policies regulating its use and access. Support information management, and development of guidelines and training materials for surveillance of HIV infection, including adaptation, review, and submission of protocols, electronic data capture (tablets), and public use database documentation.Apply all current HHS policies regulating use and access to PHIA (Personal Health Information Act) data;
Review and extend current data analytic procedures and tools of CDC and non-CDC agencies to ensure compatibility with newly developed systems;
Retrieve data and create data extracts from the data streams of PHIA data;
Develop new integrated PHIA databases for CDC or field offices;
Assist the CDC HQ, partners, and field staff to manage PHIA data;
Provide technical assistance with the integration and design of the information sources supporting various analyses;
Create data sets, subsets of larger data sets, and combinations of potentially disparate data sets;
Develop data disposition and data archival plans for data sets;
Perform data quality assurance reviews by creating and running programs to check for data errors and inconsistencies; and
Resolve any data discrepancies with the original source database and any data quality issues found in order to ensure accurate analyses.
Data Analytics: Support HIV surveillance data analysis using statistical software programs (e.g., SAS and STATA), analyze content data obtained through population-based surveillance activities to manage and analyze public health databases. Assist with data management and analysis of multiple study-related datasets, including performing quality assurance procedures, generating progress reports, data documentation and conducting basic analyses.Perform data management and data quality assurance activities including development of data quality reports and investigation and resolution of data anomalies or errors;
Communicate with project management staff, researchers, and data collectors regarding data quality issues and assist with tracking problem resolution to improve data quality;
Receive datasets and plan and conduct data cleaning and documentation of issues in consultation with project management staff;
Assist in developing Standard Operating Procedures (SOP) for data documentation, data dictionaries, and routine reports
Develop and present analytical data files to project managers and researchers.
Collaborate with multi-disciplinary, international teams of epidemiologists, statisticians, implanting partners, and other study staff to produce high-quality study datasets and documentation.
Collaborate with teams to analyze data including but not limited to analysis as directed by other team members and interpretation of analytic results
Lead analyses in collaboration with other team members
Guide analytic framework and preparation and stewardship of analytic and primary datasets
Provide development and review of data management sections of manuscripts and protocols
 Data Use:Provide technical assistance on HIV general population surveillance and estimation, including interpretation and reporting of results,
Maintain a collection of research data through databases and other repository means.
 Data Dissemination:Write and review final reports, public use database supporting materials, scientific abstracts and manuscripts.
Training and Support: Subject matter expertise in public health data, data systems, and data management capacity within CDC HQ, CDC Field offices and among multiple implementing partners for single- and multi-data management, analysis, and use to identify needs for technical assistance.Support updates to training manuals, SOPs, and other technical documents for data management of HIV surveillance.
Support in-country training of field teams to conduct HIV surveillance activities, and data analysis and data use training workshops as required.
 EDUCATION, REQUIREMENTS, AND QUALIFICATIONS
 Minimum Qualification (Required):Master’s degree in Public Health, or related health sciences field.
Three years of experience in public health data management.
Proficient in statistical software programs (e.g., SAS, STATA, and/or -R)
Excellent verbal and written communications skills. Proficient with MS Office Suite

This is an Associate Director level position managing Programming teams and providing statistical programming support for clinical study reports, integrated summary of safety (ISS), integrated summary of efficacy (ISE) and post marketing analysis needs. Key responsibilities and skills include, but are not limited to:
Responsible for the setup and monitoring of the assigned projects;
Managing overall project to ensure the deliverables meets required quality and timeline;
Conduct the meetings with Statisticians and Programmers for business needs;
Manage resources throughout the life cycle of the projects;
Coordinate client activities related to the projects;
Develop and implement standard operating procedures for Programming operation;
Lead or support electronic submission as needed;
Innovative and be able to take initiatives and follow through in Programming work flow optimization; Hire, train and mentor statistical Programming staff.
Qualifications
BS or MS degree in computer science, statistics or related field.
Four plus years of related management experience.
Excellent problem-solving skills and and high ability to work independently.
Experience in clinical trial setting.

We are seeking a talented Senior Statistical Programmer/Analyst (REMOTE) to work on client projects in our office or remotely. It's a great opportunity to work across clinical trial phases and multiple therapeutic areas in a cohesive team environment. Duties include but are not limited to:
Annotate Case Report Form (acrf.pdf) following FDA/CDISC or sponsor guidelines and create tables, listings and figures for clinical study reports with no supervision;
Independently create or validate SDTM specifications and datasets, as well as, ADaM specifications and datasets with no supervision;
Create FDA submission packages, e.g., define.xml or define.pdf following FDA/CDISC guidelines or sponsor requirements with no supervision;
Serve as point of contact (POC) of programming with statisticians for statistical input and answer technical questions and resolve technical issues from cross functional members;
Follow and reinforce regulatory agency requirements provide technical guidance; contributing to department initiatives and project deliverables, timelines and resources;
Requirements
Bachelor’s/Master’s degree in Statistics, Computer Science, Electrical and Computer Engineering, Biotechnology or related scientific disciplines with 5+ years of clinical programming (SAS) experience;
Expert-level in decoding programming logic and code and able to explain to team members; Database programming experience is a plus;
In-depth knowledge of ICH, Good Clinical Practices, Clinical research, Clinical trial process and related regulatory requirements and terminology;
Good understanding of clinical drug development process;
Strong communication and coordination skills; Independently communicate with global teams;
Detail-oriented and ability to learn and adapt to changes;
Proficient in Microsoft Office Suite, e.g. Word, Excel, PowerPoint, etc.
